shared_text:
Kenesaw Blue Devil Volleyball
15 hrs ¬∑

Varsity played in the Friend tournament this morning!

Started out the day playing Humphrey Lindsay Holy Family. The girls played 2 hard fought games but came up just short, 23-25, 24-26.

They then went on to play Freeman and dropped those sets 23-25, 15-25.

The girls continue to work hard and learn new things we can improve on!

Big week ahead for the Lady Blue!

Tuesday 9/15 we will be traveling to NELSON for a triangular. NO JV
5:30 vs L-N
6:30 vs Harvard

Thursday 9/17 we travel to Franklin for another triangular. JV will for sure play Franklin we are waiting to hear about Deshler
6 vs Deshler
7 vs Franklin

Saturday the Varsity will travel to play the Central Valley tournament. Times TBD.

Go Blue Devils!! üèêüíô

Jv beat Arcadia/Loup City in 2-1 sets! Lost to Amherst 1-2 but played some very competitive volleyball and never gave up!

Dear Parents,

Kenesaw Booster Club is selling personalized gym towels to encourage good hygiene during COVID-19.

We have contacted the fall sport coaches to send home an order form THIS WEEK! We want students to have them available for the start of fall sports.

We will do a later order as well.

Orders due by Friday, July 31st to the Kenesaw school office.
Payment is due at the time of order.

If your child does not bring home an order form and you want him/her to have one at the start of school, please message here and we can email you a form.

post_text:
The Hosier family has lost many items from their home due to the recent flooding. Their son is going to be a sophomore and is a part of the Kenesaw School family. The family was fortunate enough to save most of their clothing and toys for the kids, however, they had extensive damage to the house, and lost most major appliances.
We will be collecting monetary donations at the school until Friday, June 5, to help the family. Donations can be dropped off at the school during normal business hours. Please call ahead of time to let the school know you are coming or if you have any questions; (402) 752-3215. Thank you in advance for helping out a member of the Kenesaw School Family.

The Nebraska Department of Education is seeking feedback to help school districts address immediate needs in response to the coronavirus pandemic.

The United States Congress passed the Coronavirus Aid, Relief, And Economic Security (CARES) Act, which includes one-time relief funding for local school districts, intended to address challenges of providing education during the COVID-19 pandemic.

The NDE is asking for responses through a short survey to understand local needs as well as potential investments and support. The survey is available in English and Spanish on the department‚Äôs website: https://nde.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_efislqh4QDEA1KZ.



Everyone is encouraged to fill out the survey by Monday, May 11, 2020.

The Nebraska School Activities Association (NSAA) is pleased to announce the student recipients of the Winter 2019-20 Nebraska Chiropractic Physicians Association (NCPA) Academic All-State Awards. Since 2006 this NSAA Award Program has recognized students who meet the criteria for nomination by their school in the season of their activity. Each year the NSAA and the NCPA recognize students during Fall, Winter and Spring Seasons who are nominated by their schools for their individual academic excellence, leadership and significant contributions in their NSAA activity.

Boys Basketball - Deric Goldenstein
Girls Basketball - Hope Nienhueser
- Cassidy Gallagher
Speech - Jenna Jaeschke
- Paityn Jameson
Wrestling - Sean Duffy

post_text:
Virtual Graduation ‚Äì We are currently working on creating a virtual graduation to take place at 2:00 p.m. on May 16, 2020. This is the original time and date for graduation. You will be able to access it via the Kenesaw school website and social media. If you are unable to watch it at 2:00 p.m., you will still be able to watch it at your convenience.

Formal Graduation ‚Äì Currently we are working with the graduating class and their parents/guardians to schedule a formal graduation date sometime between the dates of July 18, 2020 and August 1, 2020.

Prom ‚Äì With the suggestion from the Governor and Commissioner of Education not to schedule any school activities until mid July or early August, it is highly unlikely we will be able to schedule a normal prom. We are currently working on options to have some type of celebration.

We will only allow ten students/parents in at a time; please wait in your vehicle for your turn. We are accepting donations of non-perishable goods for the community. Enter/Exit at main door only.

post_text: The after school 4-H club worked on blocks for a Quilts of Valor project. (The mission of the Quilts of Valor Foundation is to cover service members and veterans touched by war with comforting and healing Quilts of Valor.) On Thursday, February 27, club members attentively sewed strips onto blocks, completing enough blocks for one quilt, plus additional blocks. The blocks will be sewn together by a quilting group and the completed quilt will be given to an Adams County serviceman or servicewoman when completed.
